"title": "8729: enemies, of Jesus Christ",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8729: enemies, of jesus christ",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Throughout his life Jesus Christ was opposed by both spiritual and human enemies. He overcame every enemy so that his people might be set free by his victory.</p>\n<h2>The enemies of the infant Jesus</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:13-Matt2:20\">MAT 2:13–2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:14-Matt2:20\">MAT 2:14–2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:1-Rev12:5\">REV 12:1–12:5</a></p>\n<h2>Satan as the enemy of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>In the temptation in the wilderness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:12-Mark1:13\">MRK 1:12–1:13</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:11\">MAT 4:1–4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:13\">LUK 4:1–4:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:15\">GEN 3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Operating through Jesus Christ's friends</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:22-Matt16:23\">MAT 16:22–16:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:3\">LUK 22:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:21-John13:27\">JHN 13:21–13:27</a></p>\n<h2>The Jewish leaders as enemies of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>They plotted to kill Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:14\">MAT 12:14</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:6\">MRK 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:11\">LUK 6:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:2\">PSA 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:3\">ISA 53:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:1\">MAT 27:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:18\">JHN 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:1\">JHN 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:19\">JHN 7:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:53\">JHN 11:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21-1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:21–2:24</a></p>\n<h3>They had no real reason for hating him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:25\">JHN 15:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:19\">PSA 35:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:4\">PSA 69:4</a></p>\n<h2>Judas as the enemy of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:14-Matt26:16\">MAT 26:14–26:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:4\">MAT 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:36\">MAT 10:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:6\">MIC 7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:21-Matt26:25\">MAT 26:21–26:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:47-Matt26:50\">MAT 26:47–26:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:25-John13:27\">JHN 13:25–13:27</a></p>\n<h2>The enemies of Jesus Christ succeeded in killing him in accordance with God's will</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ was crucified</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:22\">MAT 27:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:1\">MRK 15:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:28-John18:32\">JHN 18:28–18:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ did not retaliate but prayed for his enemies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ can change an enemy into a friend</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:23\">GAL 1:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:1-Acts9:6\">ACT 9:1–9:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:4-Acts22:5\">ACT 22:4–22:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:9-Acts26:11\">ACT 26:9–26:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:10\">ROM 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:18\">PHP 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:24\">COL 1:24</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ will ultimately conquer all his enemies</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:25-1Cor15:26\">1CO 15:25–15:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:9\">PSA 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:2\">MAL 3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:44\">MAT 22:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:34\">ACT 2:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:6-2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:6–1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:3-2Thess2:8\">2TH 2:3–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:13\">HEB 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:13\">HEB 10:13</a></p>",
